# Required context

Align with these project docs before non-trivial work:

- **CLAUDE.md** — product overview, tech stack, workspace summary, file map, app flows, do-not-change list
- **agents.md** — data, auth, menu editor, subscriptions, packages, AI; feature checklist
- **`.cursor/rules/workspace-packages.mdc`** — full `@minute-menus/*` map

Do not duplicate architecture in chat — grep source files for implementation details. Prefer minimal scoped diffs.

## Hard constraints

- Production data via the Supabase service layer — not mockData, not localStorage (except pending-restaurant-name after OAuth)
- Customer reel dish display limit is a product requirement — do not raise without approval
- Pinned Claude model — change only when the user explicitly asks
- Menu save sends the full tree; omitted items may be deleted in the database
- Never expose Supabase service role key in client-side code
- **Vercel Hobby: max 12 serverless functions** — each `api/**/*.ts` file counts as one; at limit today; consolidate with `?action=` before adding routes (see **`.cursor/rules/vercel-api-and-crons.mdc`**)
- Engineering norms — **SOLID, DRY, KISS, YAGNI**, fail-fast stance, cyclomatic complexity limits, and change discipline live in **`coding-standards.mdc`** (and `.claude/rules/coding-standards.md`)

## Navigation

Large files (owner dashboard, supabase-service package): grep first, read targeted sections only.
